## 2026-04-03 - ExportPanel multi-collection save silently partially succeeds when set creation fails
- Replaced the `.catch(() => console.warn(...))` on set creation with a catch that re-throws for non-409 errors. 409 (set already exists) is silently swallowed — that's fine. All other set creation errors now propagate and abort the loop immediately (fail-fast). Also wrapped the batch save in a `.catch()` that re-throws with the set name in the message, so the error shown to the user identifies which collection failed. The operation is now all-or-nothing: either all collections save or none after the failing one does.
- Files changed: `packages/figma-plugin/src/ui/components/ExportPanel.tsx` ~L5 (ApiError import), ~L482–490 (set creation catch), ~L526–530 (batch save catch)
- **Learnings for future iterations:**

